	The Iditarod, named after an gold-mining ghost town,  
commemorates the effort of mushers in relaying diphtheria serum to 
Nome during a 1925 epidemic. The race began in 1973, and is run 
along historic trails traveled by gold prospectors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
