<HEADLINE> Sydney Bid Investigation Delayed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- The report from an independent inquiry  
into Sydney's successful bid for the 2000 Olympics will be delayed 
four days, organizing committee president Michael Knight said 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Knight, who called for the audit of about 3,000 pages of bid  
documents after the bribes scandal engulfed the International 
Olympic Committee, said Tom Sheridan would release his findings on 
March 15. Sheridan had been expected to report on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Mr. Sheridan rang me this afternoon and said he would prefer  
that the deadline for the delivery of the report to the SOCOG board 
be extended, and on behalf of the board I have agreed,'' Knight 
said in a statement. 
</P>
