<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EST  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Dow Falls; Nasdaq Jumps  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Nasdaq composite index closed sharply  
higher, today after Intel's proposed deal with federal regulators 
sparked a rally in technology shares. But the Dow Jones industrials 
lagged the broader market, closing lower after making spectacular 
gains last week. The Dow industrials fell 8.47 to close at 
9,727.61. NYSE decliners led advancers 1,602-1,361. The Nasdaq 
index rose 60.51 to 2,397.62. 

</P>
