<HEADLINE> Bengals Sign DL Oliver Gibson </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CINCINNATI (AP) -- The Cincinnati Bengals signed their first free  
agent of the offseason Monday, agreeing to terms with defensive 
lineman Oliver Gibson. 
</P>
<P>
	Gibson, a backup nose tackle with the Pittsburgh Steelers for  
the past four seasons, agreed to a three-year contract. Terms 
weren't disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
	The Bengals lost safety Sam Shade and end Clyde Simmons off a  
defense that was last in the NFL at stopping the run and 28th 
overall. Cincinnati gave up 28.3 points per game, most in the 
league. 
</P>
<P>
	Nose tackle Kimo von Oelhoffen started every game last season,  
but had only 45 tackles -- ninth on the team -- and no sacks. The 
Bengals allowed an average of 163.3 yards rushing per game. 
</P>
<P>
	Gibson, 26, has been primarily the backup to Joel Steed in  
Pittsburgh. He's reunited with Dick LeBeau, who was his defensive 
coordinator for two years in Pittsburgh. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's been frustrating for me behind Joel, because I know I can  
play,'' Gibson said. ``I think the Bengals have one of the fastest 
defenses in the NFL, and it's great to be back with coach LeBeau. I 
just like his style and the way he coaches.'' 
</P>
<P>
	LeBeau said Gibson could play either nose tackle or end.  
</P>
</TEXT>
