<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tom Hanks Hospitalized for Blister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Tom Hanks was hospitalized Monday for an  
infected blister he got while shooting a movie in Fiji, his 
publicist said. 
</P>
<P>
	Hanks, 42, was told to remain overnight but will miss the  
Academy Awards luncheon and the NATO Star of the Decade Awards in 
Las Vegas later this week, spokeswoman Leslee Dart said. 
</P>
<P>
	Hanks got a small blister on his right knee sometime last week  
while filming ``Cast Away.'' He wasn't able to keep the blister 
properly dressed because of the tropical climate and frequent 
filming in water, Ms. Dart said. 
</P>
<P>
	When he returned to Los Angeles, it apparently became infected  
and Hanks sought care at an undisclosed hospital on Sunday. Doctors 
advised him to stay off his feet for about a week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
