<DOCNO> APW19990308.0230 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-08 15:16:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Burns at L.A. Sports Arena </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A smoky fire devoured stacks of roofing  
insulation atop unfinished Staples Center on Monday, but damage was 
considered minor and there should be no delays in opening the new 
home for basketball's Los Angeles Lakers and Clippers, and hockey's 
Los Angeles Kings. 
</P>
<P>
	Black, greasy smoke spewed into the downtown sky from the arena  
shortly after 8 a.m. Fifty firefighters had the blaze out in 41 
minutes without injury, city fire spokesman Brian Humphrey said. 
</P>
<P>
	Stacks of plastic-wrapped, 4-by-8-foot insulation sheets went up  
in flames. Arena spokesman Michael Roth said the loss is $25,000 to 
$50,000. 
</P>
<P>
	``The blaze was attributed to an electrical problem,'' although  
investigators did not immediately specify the problem, Humphrey 
said. ``We do know that there was wiring and cabling in the area.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The building appeared undamaged, Humphrey said.  
</P>
<P>
	``I would describe the structure as rock solid,'' he said.  
</P>
<P>
	Kevin Murphy, vice president in charge of development for the  
center, said some of the sheet metal decking of the roof might have 
to be replaced because of possible heat damage. 
</P>
<P>
	The $350 million arena is expected to open in October.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
