<HEADLINE> Dow Down 18 but Nasdaq Is Up 20 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened mixed. The Dow Jones  
industrial average is down 18 points in today's early going. 
Advancers and decliners are evenly split on the New York Stock 
Exchange. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 20 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up one point. 
</P>
<P>
	With a gain of about 2.7 percent, the Dow would clear the 10,000  
mark for the first time. 
</P>
<P>
	It probably won't get there today.  
</P>
<P>
	The early read is for just a modest move for the market today.  
</P>
<P>
	The Dow gained about 460 points over the past two sessions,  
closing at a record high on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The S&AMP;P 500 begins about four points shy of its highest close  
ever. 
</P>
<P>
	Bond prices are higher. Most overseas stock markets are lower.  
</P>
</TEXT>
