<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock Market, 
and American Stock Exchange. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Delphi Financial rose 4 to 32.    	
</P>
<P>
	The stock recovered from the battering it suffered last week,  
but the controversy underlying its drop isn't over. The stock fell 
last week on speculation that Delphi's Unicover Managers Inc. 
reinsurance unit had suffered a $1.5 billion loss. While Delphi 
emphasized that Unicover's problems should affect the parent 
company, analysts warned that Delphi could still lose fee income. 

</P>
<P>
 *EMC Corp. rose 6 7/16 to 111.    	
</P>
<P>
	SunGard Recovery Services Inc., announced a new computer data  
recovery system that uses EMC's storage technology. 

</P>
<P>
 *Hartford Life Inc. rose 5/8 to 55 7/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The life insurance company agreed with American Funds Group,  
Franklin Templeton, and Massachusetts Financial Services to form a 
jointly managed variable annuity. 

</P>
<P>
 *EG&AMP;G rose 5/16 to 27 7/8.  
</P>
<P>
 *Perkin-Elmer Corp. fell 1/4 to 92 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
	EG&AMP;G Inc. plans to buy Perkin-Elmer's analytical instruments  
division for $425 million. In a press release, EG&AMP;G also said it 
will explore the possible sale of its technical services unit. 

</P>
<P>
 *Newcourt Credit rose 13/16 to 26 5/8.  
</P>
<P>
 *CIT Group fell 5/8 to 30 3/16. 
</P>
<P>
	CIT Group plans to acquire Newcourt in a stock swap valued at $9  
billion. The companies said Newcourt expects cost savings of $150 
million from the merger. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *CNET rose 40 1/8 to 208 1/8.    	
</P>
<P>
	The Internet publisher's 2-for-1 stock split, announced in  
mid-February, became effective late Monday. 

</P>
<P>
 *Novell Inc. rose 3 3/16 to 23 5/16.    	
</P>
<P>
	The stock rose following a positive Barron's cover story on the  
networking software company's transformation under Chief Executive 
Officer Eric Schmidt. Novell has had six successive quarters of 
``impressive results,'' including success with its NetWare 5.0 
network software, released last September, according to the 
Barron's article. In separate news, the company said it is testing 
its next-generation Internet directory, which it said eliminates 
the need for special-purpose Internet directories. 

</P>
<P>
 *7th Street.com rose 3 27/32 to 8 27/32.    	
</P>
<P>
	The company agreed to offer Web multimedia training to America  
Online Inc.'s users through its Tutorials.com Internet personal 
tutorial product, analysts said. A Business week article said that 
other major Internet and technology companies, including a 
blue-chip giant, a leading computer maker and a major Web service 
provider, are soon to sign pacts with 7thStreet.com. 

</P>
<P>
 *Onsale Inc. rose 15 3/8 to 47 1/4.    	
</P>
<P>
	Internet-related stocks surged amid a general rally in  
technology shares. In addition, Internet retailer Onsale reported 
that more than ten million bids had been placed on its atAuction 
service at www.onsale.com. 

</P>
