<HEADLINE> SLOC Hires Bill Wagner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- The man who helped Olympic organizers  
draft their budget and map out planning has been hired as senior 
vice president of operations for the 2002 Winter Games. 
</P>
<P>
	The Salt Lake Organizing Committee on Monday announced Bill  
Wagner's promotion from managing director of operations to senior 
vice president. 
</P>
<P>
	Wagner will take over most of the responsibilities of former  
SLOC senior vice president Dave Johnson, who was forced to resign 
Jan. 8 because of his role in Salt Lake's tainted bid effort. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm enthused and excited to be part of the 2002 Games,''  
Wagner said. 
</P>
<P>
	He has more than 20 years of experience in operations and  
project management with Bechtel Corp., which received $750,000 from 
the SLOC to help craft the committee's budget. 
</P>
<P>
	The California-based engineering and consulting firm aided  
organizers of the Summer Games in Los Angeles in 1984 and in 
Barcelona in 1992. 
</P>
<P>
	Wagner, who headed Bechtel's consulting project for the SLOC,  
will take a leave of absence from the firm to join the organizing 
committee full time. 
</P>
<P>
	While he was the SLOC's managing director of operations, Wagner  
had remained under contract with Bechtel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
