<HEADLINE> Yankees' Strawberry Set to Play </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Darryl Strawberry's comeback from colon  
cancer will come sooner than expected. 
</P>
<P>
	New York manager Joe Torre said Monday night that Strawberry  
will start at designated hitter when the Yankees travel to Fort 
Myers on Wednesday to face the Boston Red Sox. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was thinking more toward the middle of the month, but Darryl  
said he was ready,'' Torre said. ``The sooner he gets with it, the 
better chance he has of being ready.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry, also slowed in recent years by knee problems,  
resumed his running program last week. He was not expected to make 
his spring training debut until next week. 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry had colon cancer surgery last October, and will  
undergo chemotherapy through at least April. He started spring 
training as one of four candidates for what is expected to a 
left-field platoon. 
</P>
<P>
	``Even at DH, it will tell us how is knee is going to hold up  
and what his endurance is,'' Torre said. 
</P>
